            <tr><td>Hard link vs soft link</td><td class="note">Hard = same inode, persists after original deleted. Soft = pointer to path, breaks if original removed.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Permission 755</td><td class="note">Owner: rwx. Group: r-x. Others: r-x. Standard for scripts.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>chmod vs chown</td><td class="note">chmod = change permissions. chown = change ownership.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Port checker command</td><td class="note">netstat -tulnp | grep PORT, or ss -tulnp, or lsof -i :PORT</td></tr>
            <tr><td>SIGTERM vs SIGKILL</td><td class="note">SIGTERM (15) = graceful stop, can be caught. SIGKILL (9) = force kill, cannot be caught.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>zombie process</td><td class="note">Process that has finished but parent hasn't read its exit code. Shows as Z in ps.</td></tr>
