    <!-- AGENTS & NODES -->
    <div class="section">
      <div class="section-title st-jenkins">05 — Agents, nodes & master</div>
      <div class="grid2">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-title"><span class="dot dot-red"></span>Master vs Agent architecture</div>
          <table>
            <tr><th></th><th>Jenkins Master</th><th>Agent / Worker Node</th></tr>
            <tr><td class="note">Role</td><td>Schedules, coordinates</td><td>Executes actual builds</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="note">UI</td><td>Hosts Jenkins UI</td><td>No UI</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="note">Runs builds?</td><td>Should NOT (security + load)</td><td>Yes — all build work here</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="note">Connection</td><td>—</td><td>SSH or JNLP (Java agent)</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="note">Labels</td><td>—</td><td>linux, docker, windows, etc.</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="note">Dynamic?</td><td>Static</td><td>Can be dynamic (K8s, AWS)</td></tr>
          </table>
          <div class="tip-jenkins" style="margin-top:12px;"><strong>Why separate?</strong> Running builds on master risks crashing Jenkins itself. Heavy builds = high CPU/memory → master becomes unresponsive → ALL jobs fail.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-title"><span class="dot dot-purple"></span>Build triggers</div>
          <div class="cmd-row"><span class="cmd cmd-jenkins">Webhook (GitHub/GitLab)</span><span class="desc">Push-based — GitHub notifies Jenkins on commit. Fastest, preferred.</span></div>
          <div class="cmd-row"><span class="cmd cmd-jenkins">pollSCM('H/5 * * * *')</span><span class="desc">Poll-based — Jenkins checks repo every 5 mins. Slower, more load.</span></div>
          <div class="cmd-row"><span class="cmd cmd-jenkins">cron('0 2 * * *')</span><span class="desc">Scheduled build — 2am daily (nightly builds)</span></div>
          <div class="cmd-row"><span class="cmd cmd-jenkins">Upstream job</span><span class="desc">Triggered when another job completes successfully</span></div>
          <div class="cmd-row"><span class="cmd cmd-jenkins">Manual trigger</span><span class="desc">User clicks "Build Now" in Jenkins UI</span></div>
          <div class="cmd-row"><span class="cmd cmd-jenkins">Build on PR</span><span class="desc">Multibranch pipeline auto-triggers on pull request</span></div>
          <div class="tip-jenkins" style="margin-top:12px;"><strong>Webhook vs polling:</strong> Webhook = GitHub pushes notification to Jenkins (instant). Polling = Jenkins keeps asking GitHub (delay + API rate limits). Always prefer webhook in production.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CREDENTIALS & SECURITY -->
    <div class="section">
      <div class="section-title st-jenkins">06 — Credentials & security</div>
      <div class="grid2">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-title"><span class="dot dot-red"></span>withCredentials — inject secrets safely</div>
          <div class="code-block">
<span class="cmt">// Username + Password (Docker, DB)</span>
<span class="kw-jenkins">withCredentials</span>([usernamePassword(
    credentialsId: <span class="str">'docker-creds'</span>,
    usernameVariable: <span class="str">'USER'</span>,
    passwordVariable: <span class="str">'PASS'</span>
)]) {
    sh <span class="str">'docker login -u $USER -p $PASS'</span>
}

<span class="cmt">// Secret text (API key, token)</span>
<span class="kw-jenkins">withCredentials</span>([string(
    credentialsId: <span class="str">'api-token'</span>,
    variable: <span class="str">'TOKEN'</span>
)]) {
    sh <span class="str">'curl -H "Auth: $TOKEN" https://api.example.com'</span>
}

<span class="cmt">// SSH private key</span>
<span class="kw-jenkins">withCredentials</span>([sshUserPrivateKey(
    credentialsId: <span class="str">'prod-ssh'</span>,
    keyFileVariable: <span class="str">'KEY'</span>
)]) {
    sh <span class="str">'ssh -i $KEY user@prod-server ./deploy.sh'</span>
}</div>
          <div class="warn"><strong>Never:</strong> hardcode passwords in Jenkinsfile. They appear in logs, Git history, and are a major security risk.</div>
        </div>
